How to write a servlet class
1. Servlet interface 
2. Genric Servlets (AbstractClass)
3. Http Servlet (abstract Class)


A. Servlet Interface:

There are 5 abstract methods:
    1. void init(ServletConfig config);
    2. void service(ServletRequest, ServletResponse);
    3. void destroy();
    4. String getServletInfo();
    5. ServletConfig getServletConfig();
    
    
    
    
B. Generic Servlet:

This class implements Servlets:
Only Single abstract method is: service(ServletRequest, ServletResponse);
So we only have to implement this methods


C. HttpServlet:

    The HttpServlet class extends the GenericServlet class and implements Serializable interface.
    
        abstract methods: 1. doGet(HttpServletRequest, HttpServletResponse);
                          2. doPost(HttpServletRequest, HttpServletResponse);